The paper deals with aspect-based sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method utilizes unsupervised machine learning techniques, which involve clustering and similarity measures, indicating the relevance of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) subcategories. The paper also mentions the use of cosine similarity measure, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and similarity measures (cs.SI) subcategories.
